The probability \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\) is determined using the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\). This implies \(P(X_i \leq 27.3) = 0.7\) for each observation \(X_i\).

The event \(Y_7 < 27.3\) is equivalent to at least seven observations being less than or equal to 27.3. Since the distribution is continuous, \(P(X_i < 27.3) = P(X_i \leq 27.3) = 0.7\), and the equality case has probability zero.

Let \(S\) be the number of observations \(\leq 27.3\), so \(S \sim \text{Binomial}(n=8, p=0.7)\). Then:
\[
P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(S \geq 7) = P(S=7) + P(S=8).
\]

Calculate:
\[
P(S=7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3,
\]
\[
P(S=8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0 = (0.7)^8.
\]

Compute the powers:
\[
(0.7)^7 = 0.0823543,
\]
\[
(0.7)^8 = 0.05764801.
\]

Then:
\[
P(S=7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 0.19765032,
\]
\[
P(S=8) = 0.05764801.
\]

Sum the probabilities:
\[
P(S \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833.
\]

Rounding to three significant figures gives 0.255.

