- 17% have an irregular heartbeat (I).
- Of those with an irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure, so the joint probability of irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure is 35% × 17% = 5.95%.
- Of those with normal blood pressure (N), 11% have an irregular heartbeat. Since normal blood pressure is 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%, the joint probability of irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure is 11% × 65% = 7.15%.

