 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The lengths of life for bulbs from company A and B are normally distributed and independent. Let \(X \sim N(800, 14400)\) and \(Y \sim N(850, 2500)\). The difference \(D = X - Y\) follows a normal distribution with mean \(\mu_D = 800 - 850 = -50\) and variance \(\sigma_D^2 = 14400 + 2500 = 16900\), so standard deviation \(\sigma_D = \sqrt{16900} = 130\).

The probability that \(X\) exceeds \(Y\) by at least 15 hours is \(P(D > 15)\). Standardizing gives:
\[
