\[
Z = \frac{15 + 50}{130} = \frac{65}{130} = 0.5
\]
Thus, \(P(D > 15) = P(Z > 0.5)\), where \(Z\) is a standard normal variable. Using the standard normal distribution, \(P(Z > 0.5) = 1 - P(Z \leq 0.5) = 1 - 0.6915 = 0.3085\).

