- P(L) = P(I ∩ L) + P(R ∩ L) = 19%.
- With P(I ∩ L) = 3.90%, solving for P(R ∩ L): 19% - 3.90% = 15.10%.

Thus, the percentage of patients with a regular heartbeat and low blood pressure is 15.10%. Rounding to three significant figures (consistent with input precision) gives 15.1%.

