After computing the zero-point energy (ZPE) as \( 697.025  \text{cm}^{-1} \) and converting it to eV, the result is \( 0.0864201  \text{eV} \). Adding this to \( D_0 = 2.4287  \text{eV} \) gives \( D_e = 2.5151201  \text{eV} \), which is rounded to four decimal places as \( 2.5151  \text{eV} \) to match the precision of \( D_0 \).

